\title{Right adjoints to the unit}
\taxon{theory}
\import{macros}

\p{

The \define{theory of right adjoints to the unit} is the modal double theory
#{(\dbl{T},T)} generated by

\ul{
  \li{an object #{x}}
  \li{an arrow #{\otimes: Tx \to x}}
  \li{two special cells, the \define{unit} and the \define{projections},
  \centerfigs{
  \quiverinline{
  % https://q.uiver.app/#
  \begin{tikzcd}
	x & x \\
	& Tx \\
	x & x
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\shortmid"{marking}, equals, from=1-1, to=1-2]
	\arrow[equals, from=1-1, to=3-1]
	\arrow["{\eta_x}", from=1-2, to=2-2]
	\arrow["\otimes", from=2-2, to=3-2]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\shortmid"{marking}, equals, from=3-1, to=3-2]
	\arrow["\iota"{description}, draw=none, from=0, to=1]
  \end{tikzcd}
  }
  #{\qquad\text{and}\qquad}
  \quiverinline{
  % https://q.uiver.app/#
  \begin{tikzcd}
	Tx & Tx \\
	x \\
	Tx & Tx
	\arrow[""{name=0, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\shortmid"{marking}, equals, from=1-1, to=1-2]
	\arrow["\otimes"', from=1-1, to=2-1]
	\arrow[equals, from=1-2, to=3-2]
	\arrow["{\eta_x}"', from=2-1, to=3-1]
	\arrow[""{name=1, anchor=center, inner sep=0}, "\shortmid"{marking}, equals, from=3-1, to=3-2]
	\arrow["\pi"{description}, draw=none, from=0, to=1]
  \end{tikzcd}
  }
  }
  }
}

subject to the triangle equations constituting an adjunction #{\eta_x \dashv
\otimes}
(see [Lambert & Patterson 2024](cartesian-double-theories-2024), Theory 3.6).

}
